{% call components.section("Anatomy") -%}
<p>Each stat is composed of a number or percentage and body text. A title, icon, or call to action are optional elements
    that can provide additional information.</p>

<div class="margin-bottom--7">
    <img src="{{ '/assets/statistic/stat-anatomy.svg' | url }}" alt="A stat's anatomy consists of an icon, title, number, body text, and call to action, in that order."
        style="--inline-img-max-width: 992px;">
</div>

<div class="multi-column--min-400-wide">
    <div>
        <h4>Title</h4>
        <p>If there's supporting text for the number, the words can be added as a title. For example, in the phrase
            “over 90%,” the word “over” is added as a title.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
        <h4>Number</h4>
        <p>This slot should include only digits, a percentage symbol, periods, or commas.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
        <h4>Body text</h4>
        <p>Every stat should have body text that explains the context around the number.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
        <h4>Additional elements</h4>
        <p>A stat can contain a relevant icon and/or call to action.</p>
    </div>
</div>
{%- endcall %}

